Google Earnings
---------------

From the Wall Street Journal ( https://www.wsj.com/tech/alphabet-googl-q4-e=
arnings-report-2024-284f4085 ) :

A slowdown in cloud-computing sales dragged down Google=E2=80=99s revenue g=
rowth in its most recent quarter, sending its shares tumbling in after-hour=
s trading. Parent company Alphabet reported $96.5 billion of revenue for th=
e three months ending December, an increase of 12% from the same period a y=
ear earlier. Alphabet hasn=E2=80=99t reported a growth rate that low since =
2023. Shares in Alphabet were down around 7% in after-hours trading followi=
ng the earnings report, paring much of this year=E2=80=99s gains of about 8=
%. Microsoft shares also dropped last week after investors were similarly d=
isappointed in the growth rate of its cloud business. Google=E2=80=99s clou=
d-computing division reported $12 billion in fourth-quarter sales, up 30.1%=
 from the same period a year earlier. In the third quarter, cloud sales gre=
w 35%.

Google Chief Executive Sundar Pichai said Google was accelerating its inves=
tments in the data centers that power AI, both for his company and clients =
of its cloud-computing business. Pichai said Google would spend about $75 b=
illion on capital expenditures this year, compared with $52.5 billion in 20=
24.

I think that last bit, about Google's forecast for a massive increase in ca=
pital expenditures (the Street was expecting $58 billion), probably has mor=
e to do with the stock's reaction than the Cloud miss, but to the extent it=
 is both, well, the reaction seems a bit overwrought.

Last quarter Google had arguably its best Cloud results yet, with 35% growt=
h on 17% margins; this quarter saw only 30% growth on 18% margins:

